File: Action SA. JOHANNESBURG - ActionSA says the eThekwini Municipality has used just 7% of its budget to fix the sewerage system and seven major projects have been put on hold. The party is planning on taking the municipality to court. READ: Cape Town beaches | Wastewater permit decision criticised Sewage has been flowing into rivers and the sea since last year's devastating floods. Beaches have had to be closed for fears of e-Coli in the water which has badly affected tourism.